sentences: Early years =
When Shelor was four years old, growing up in southwestern Virginia, his grandfather fashioned a banjo for him from an old pressure cooker lid.
Shelor played six years with the band.
The Virginia Squires reunited for one show in 2017.
Shelor joined the Lonesome River Band in 1990.
When founder Tim Austin left in 1995, Shelor and Ronnie Bowman managed the band management.
When Bowman left in 2000, Shelor became manager.
In 1997, Shelor released a solo album Leading Roll on the Sugar Hill label.
International Bluegrass Music Association (IBMA) Instrumental Album Of The Year award for his involvement in Knee Deep In Bluegrass on Rebel Records.
2009: inducted in to the Virginia Country Music Hall of Fame.
